histogram.summary:
Records the duration from the initial show/activation request of a new browser window to its first paint. {CreationSource}
This metric is used to measure the impact of window show deferral. It is recorded only once per window lifecycle. If multiple windows are shown during startup, e.g. due to session restore, the first window is measured in "InitialWebUI.Startup" and not in this histogram.
This is only recorded for desktop platforms when the InitialWebUIMetrics is enabled.

Records the delay between the native browser window's first presentation (paint) and the Reload Button first paint in a new window. {CreationSource}
This is a direct, session-linked measurement of the delta, unlike the separately logged `.FirstPaint` metrics. Used to quantify the rendering lag.
This is only recorded for desktop platforms when the InitialWebUIMetrics is enabled.
